1 Introduction

Capital BikeShare is a bikeshare system offering new generation of bike rentals service to customers. In this data analysis project, I attempt to find out how factors affect the number of shared bike rental and use model to predict the number of shared bike rental for a specific day.By doing this analysis, Capital Bikeshare could prepare enough bikes for the customers, and therefore improves the customer services.

  • Business Value Proposition:

2 Data Description

The data source is from capitalbikes.com. It originally has 10886 observations and 12 variables.Variables are: “datetime”,“season”,“holiday”,“workingday”,“weather”,“temp”,“atemp”,“humidity” “windspeed”,“casual”,“registered”,and “count”. * “datetime” is the date variable. * “season” is a categorical variable, in which “1” represents for spring, “2” represents for summer, “3” represents for fall,and “4” represents for winter. * “holiday” is a binary variable that tells whether the day is considered a holiday. * “workingday” is a binary that tells whether the day is neither a weekend nor holiday. * “weather” is a categorical variable. “1”is Clear, Few clouds, Partly cloudy, Partly cloudy. “2” is Mist + Cloudy, Mist + Broken clouds, Mist + Few clouds, Mist.“3”is Light Snow, Light Rain + Thunderstorm + Scattered clouds, Light Rain + Scattered clouds. “4”is Heavy Rain + Ice Pallets + Thunderstorm + Mist, Snow + Fog. * “temp”,temperature in Celsius,is a numerical variable
* “atemp” is the numerical variable that stands for “feels like” temperature in Celsius. * “humidity” is the numerical variable that stands for relative humidity * “windspeed”,wind speed, is a numerical variable. * “casual” is the numerical variable that stands for the number of non-registered user rentals initiated. * “registered” is the numerical variable that stands for the number of registered user rentals initiated. * “count” is the numerical variable that stands for the number of total rentals.

3 Data Preprocessing

3.1 variable type corretion

The variables:“season”,“holiday”,“workingday”,and “weather” are not in correct variable type, so first I need to change these categorical variables to factor.

data$season <- as.factor(data$season)
data$holiday <- as.factor(data$holiday)
data$workingday <- as.factor(data$workingday)
data$weather <- as.factor(data$weather)

3.2 create new variables

I create three new categorical variables: “Year”,“Month”, “Time”, and label them as factors so that I can analyze the their relationship with the number of shared bike rental respectively.

data$Year <- sapply(strsplit(as.character(data$datetime), "-"), "[", 1)
data$Month <- sapply(strsplit(as.character(data$datetime), "-"), "[", 2)
data$Time <- sapply(strsplit(as.character(data$datetime), " "), "[", 2)

data$Year <- as.factor(data$Year)
data$Month <- as.factor(data$Month)
data$Time <- as.factor(data$Time)

Now, check the level of the variables.

4.1.2 quantitative variables correlation

I would like to see which quantitative variables are highly correlated, especially how other variables are corralated with “casual”,“registered”,and “count”.

From the correlation plot below, I can tell that: * temperature and feel like temperature are moderately positive correlated with the number of non-registered user rentals initiated, the number of total rentals,and the number of registered user rentals initiated, respectively,all other factors equal. * The correlation between the number of non-registered user rentals and the temperature is stronger than the correlation between other variables. * “humidity” is moderately negative correlated with “casual”,“count”, and “registered”. * The correlation between "“humidity” and “casual” is stronger.“windspeed” has weak negative linear relationship with “casual”,“registered” and “count”.I will remove this variable in the model.

I can conclude that the number of shared bike rentals is moderately positively affected by temperature,“feels like” temperature, and negatively affected by humidity of a specific day. Also, temperature, “feels like” temperature, and humidity have larger effect on the number of non-registered user rentals initiated than the number of registered user rentals initiated.

plot_correlation(data,type = "c")

The results does not match with the observations from the graphs above.We get the result that humidity and the number of total shared bike rentals are negatively correlated and during workday there are more shared bike rentals than non-workday. 5 Conclusion

The goal of the project is to estimate the number of shared bike rental for a specific day for Capital Bike Share. The struggle of the Capital Bike is that the number of shared bike rental number is affected by numerical variables,such as “temperature”,“feels like” temperature, “humidity”, that are changing everyday.By using the model,the customer, Capital Bike Share, would be able to predict the number of shared bike needed by its customers with information of a day,and therefore improve the customer service.

This Data analysis help to estimate how do “season”,“holiday”,“workingday”, “weather”,“temperature”,“feels like” temperature, “humidity”,“Year”,“Month”,“Time” affect the number of Capital Bike Share rental for non-registered, registered, total users. The model I use is the stepwise regression model which matches the result from correlation plot and other graphs we plot. Also, it has better precision in RMSE calculation. In the new regression model,as temperature increases by 1 Celsius degree, the number of total shared bike rentals increase by around 2, all other factors remain equal.As “feels like” temperature increases bu 1 Celsius degree, the number of total shared bike rentals increase by 3, all other factors equal.As humidity increase by 1 unit, the number of total shared bike rentals decrease by around 1 unit , assuming everything else is constant. If it is a workday, the number of total shared bike rentals would be around 2 unit more than that of a non workday, assuming everything else is constant. If it is a holiday, the number of total shared bike rental would be around 6 unit more than that of a non holiday,assuming everything else is constant.If it is weather 2 on a day, The total number of shared bike rental would be 11 unit less than that of the weather1, assuming everything else is constant.If it is weather 3 on a day, The total number of shared bike rental would be 69 unit less than that of weather1, assuming everything else is constant.If it is weather 4 on a day, the total number of shared bike rental would be 173 unit less than that of weather1, assuming everything else is constant. During 07:00:00 to 20:00:00 customers demand most of the shared rental bikes.The peaks are 08:00:00:00 and 17:00:00 to 18:00:00

To improve the customer service, Capital Bike Share should prepare more bikes when the weather is Clear, Few clouds, Partly cloudy, Partly cloudy and when the time is 08:00:00:00 or between 17:00:00 and 18:00:00.
